WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.740
Here is the StatePort preview.

00:00:02.190 --> 00:00:05.360
It gives an AI project a place to live outside the chat.

00:00:05.810 --> 00:00:10.820
When you come back, you can see the project, what you were doing, and what needs your attention.

00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:13.730
This is the conversation screen.

00:00:14.180 --> 00:00:17.920
You can ask for help, but the conversation is only one part of the project.

00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:21.810
Your files and decisions do not disappear inside a long chat.

00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:25.390
This screen shows the project information.

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:30.840
It helps you see what is ready, what is still being checked, and what is only a test.

00:00:31.290 --> 00:00:33.750
That makes it easier to know what you can trust.

00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:36.390
And this is the mobile view.

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:39.940
The same project stays readable on a small screen.

00:00:40.390 --> 00:00:42.720
This is a local preview made on my computer.

00:00:43.170 --> 00:00:45.210
You cannot download the software yet.

00:00:45.660 --> 00:00:50.860
The point of StatePort is simple: help you pick up AI work again without losing the work itself.
